The paper deals with the performance analysis of multi-cell cooperation in wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper uses techniques from stochastic geometry and large deviation theory to analyze the outage probability. The next likely sub-categories are cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with wireless network performance and interference mitigation. The paper also mentions the use of regular lattice clustering, which falls under the sub-category cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper may also fall under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia), as it deals with wireless communication and signal diversity.
